=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Guides_FilterComparisons_ex3 ===

DESCRIPTION: A neutral pure_tone sound, with sine_like oscillator character around 180 Hz, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally sparse.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: neutral
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: sparse
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 180.2501
  harmonic_decay_rate: -3.6381
  harmonic_regularity: 0.9417
  pitch_clarity: 81.2769
  inharmonicity: 0.4260
  type: sine_like
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -21.5033
  resonance_freq: 473.7305

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Filter Comparisons Example 3
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Guides/FilterComparisons.html
// Tags: FilterComparisons, Guides, filter
// ---
// --- Example 3 ---
(
{
    NLFiltC.ar(
        LFSaw.ar([120, 180], 0, mul:0.1),
        0.5,
        -0.04,
        0.8,
        0.2,
        LFCub.kr(0.2, [0, 0.5 * pi], 63, 103)
    )
}.play
)
